{"id": 6722, "title": "Ticket #6722: HTCondor does not support s3 URLs", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe function that determines whether a string is a URL disallows valid protocols such as s3\n\n<p>This ticket inspired by the following github pull request: <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/pull/23\">https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/pull/23</a></p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2018-Jul-30 10:22:42 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-3.1\">https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-3.1</a>\n\n<p>Jaime believes that the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=NorduGrid\" title=\"Nordu Grid\">NorduGrid</a></span> code shouldn't have any problems as a result of updating <code>IsUrl()</code> to match reality.  TJ believes the same of the file transfer code; those two appear to be the main two users of this code.\n\n</p><p>If we already link libcurl to condor_utils, we should just replace <code>IsUrl()</code> with  the appropriate method(s) from libcurl.  Otherwise, we should reimplement.\n\n</p><p></p><hr/>\n<em>2018-Aug-21 11:53:56 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE and DOC REVIEW:</strong> Looks good.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Aug-21 10:45</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5d104678f974f003804443da3891cac815bff8b0\">[55316]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6722'); return false;\" title=\"HTCondor does not support s3 URLs\">#6722</a></span>